===message:Kristin, yes the age of consumerism and materialism had definitely started in the 1950’s and had blossomed during the “Thirty Glorious Years.”  The Thirty Glorious Years may be over but consumerism definitely has not left us.  Just last night I was watching a television miniseries that had commercial breaks that were just as long as the movie itself!  This is very annoying to me as I’m sure it is to countless others.  I guess this type of spending really helps boost the economy, but where it might help the economy, I’m sure it hurts us moralistically.  We as individuals, feel cheated if we don’t have what the TV is telling us everyone else wants and/or has, and this can rearrange our priorities in a negative way.  What’s more, if we are not careful, we can get ourselves in a whole lot of debt by the all-to-easy temptation to “charge it.”   
=========yorg=========
