===message:Yes the credit card is a dangerous  item in the hands of someone who is easily influenced by what their neighbors have. So many people today are refinancing their homes to get enough money to pay off  their credit cards , but the problem seems to be that not everyone that does this cuts up the credit card and closes the account. The result of course is these people are then in debt again  to the credit card company and have also used up equity they had in their home. I do not think this was the general plan when credit was extended to people in the 1950s. 

